member.name: T:BRISK.Branzfire.System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.Utilities.HistogramChartHelper
member.summary:
Helper class that creates a histogram chart. Histogram is a data distribution chart which shows how many values, from the data series, are inside each segment interval.
You can define how many intervals you want to have using the SegmentIntervalNumber field or the exact length of the interval using the SegmentIntervalWidth field. Actual segment interval number can be slightly different due to the automatic interval rounding.

member.name: F:BRISK.Branzfire.System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.Utilities.HistogramChartHelper.SegmentIntervalNumber
member.summary: Number of class intervals the data range is devided in. This property only has affect when "SegmentIntervalWidth" is set to double.NaN.

member.name: F:BRISK.Branzfire.System.Windows.Forms.DataVisualization.Charting.Utilities.HistogramChartHelper.SegmentIntervalWidth
member.summary: Histogram class interval width. Setting this value to "double.NaN" will result in automatic width calculation based on the data range and number of required interval specified in "SegmentIntervalNumber".
